text: Paddock in the grounds of Swangrove House Swangrove is a Grade I listed country house in Hawkesbury, South Gloucestershire, England. The listing includes Swangrove House, its garden walls, four corner pavilions, and gate piers. It was built in 1703 by William Killigrew of Bath. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Country houses in Gloucestershire Category:Grade I listed buildings in Gloucestershire Category:Grade I listed houses Category:Houses completed in 1703 Category:1703 establishments in England
